        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-04-24 21:13:08.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-3221 lov: remove set_fs() call from lov_getstripe()",
        "message": "LU-3221 lov: remove set_fs() call from lov_getstripe()\n\nlov_getstripe() calls set_fs(KERNEL_DS) so that it can handle a struct\nlov_user_md pointer from user- or kernel-space.  This changes the\nbehavior of copy_from_user() on SPARC and may result in a misaligned\naccess exception which in turn oopses the kernel.  In fact the\nrelevant argument to lov_getstripe() is never called with a\nkernel-space pointer and so changing the address limits is unnecessary\nand so we remove the calls to save, set, and restore the address\nlimits.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id23f429875c92f9d6ed5cd06cadd741d98c46074\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
